member.name: IInspectable.GetIids
member.summary: Gets the interfaces that are implemented by the current Windows Runtime class.
member.param: The number of interfaces that are implemented by the current Windows Runtime object, excluding the and implementations.
A pointer to an array that contains an IID for each interface implemented by the current Windows Runtime object. The and interfaces are excluded.

returns.para: This function can return the following values.

listheader.description: The IID array was allocated and saved in iids successfully.

member.name: IInspectable.GetRuntimeClassName
member.summary: Gets the fully qualified name of the current Windows Runtime object.
member.param: The fully qualified name of the current Windows Runtime object.

returns.para: This function can return the following values.

listheader.description: The className string was created successfully.
className refers to a class factory or a static interface.

member.name: IInspectable.GetTrustLevel
member.summary: Gets the trust level of the current Windows Runtime object.
member.param: The trust level of the current Windows Runtime object. The default is BaseLevel.

member.name: IInspectable
member.summary: Provides functionality required for all Windows Runtime classes.
